Business Brief -- B.F. Goodrich Co.:
   Firm Says Operating Loss
   In Quarter Due to Plastics
Last month, Goodrich said it would take a fourth-quarter
charge of $77.9 million, or $3.07 a share, to halt production
of polyvinyl chloride plastic at three sites in the U.S.
Goodrich also said it would trim 225 jobs over two years tied
to the plant closings.
   In 1990, Goodrich had fourth-quarter net income of $14.1
million, or 47 cents a share, and full-year net of $136.3
million, or $5.04 a share.